      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm so sorry you're feeling this way, and I hear how exhausted and overwhelmed you are right now. It sounds like everything feels like it's crumbling beneath your feet, and that kind of weight can make even the smallest steps feel impossible. Please know that your feelings are valid, and you don't have to carry this alone.\n\nYou mentioned wanting everything to stop, and I want to gently remind you that while it feels like there's no finish line, there are people who care deeply about your well-being and want to help you navigate this. If you're feeling like you might hurt yourself or can't cope, please reach out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional immediately. You can also contact a crisis line like 988 in the US or similar services in your country for immediate support.\n\nEven though things feel like they've fallen apart, there are still moments of strength within you, and it's okay to take it one small step at a time. Sometimes, just pausing and resting can help you find a new perspective. You are not alone in this, and there are resources ready to help you when you're ready to reach out.",
      "source": "target",
